comments.text:
I bet Drake was lying down on a towel by the ocean, just soaking up some sun. Suddenly a huge shadow was cast over him, he open his eyes and lowered his tanning tray and was star struck by what he saw. It was none other than Bartleby Montclair of Dresden, the richest and sexiest man who ever lived, towering over him. Drake probably stammered as he tried to speak in the presence of this God among men. Bartleby, with a gentle smile on his face, no doubt pressed his index finger against Drake's lips as he shushed him. Suddenly Drake was scooped up and nestled between Bartleby's powerful arms and pectorals. 

Bartleby spoke in a soothing voice, "The people are worried about you, Drake. Lets not keep them waiting.", to which Drake simply nodded his head as a single tear slid down his cheek. Drake drifted off to sleep as Bartleby carried him off into the sunset. Every so often, Bartleby could hear Drake singing the lyrics to the Sonic Underground theme song in his sleep, but to the beat and pacing of the Drake & Josh theme song. It was the second most beautiful sound Bartleby had ever heard, with the first of course being the sound of Sonic's cheeks clapping.
